  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Regulatory requirements are documented in the inline requirement object (https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou1-hemolysis-req) which specifies RH < 1 acceptance criterion against predicate device performance. The UoA binds a validated CFD model and experimental hemolysis dataset.",
